Linux is case sensitive unlike sql
echo : acts like print 
whoami : prints the username 
id : print unique id , group id and group you have joined 
id root : root is superuser like administator of the system
id -un : prints only current username
pwd : prints working directory
echo ~ : prints home directory
ls : lists all files and directories in your current working directory
ls ~ : lists from home directory
cd: used to change directory
.. : directory above
cd .. : move one level to parent directory
~ : shortcut for homedirectory 
cd ~ : goes to home directory 
touch filename : used to create new empty files 
